  "content_markdown": "Version: 8.1\nOn this page\nLevel: beginner\nSections are structural components of the app that are connected to an object, list page, and one or more form pages. Section setup is crucial for end user experience with your app. Certain app templates already come with a section. You can add more sections based on new or existing objects.\nExample\nCreate a \"Financial benefits\" app based on **Records & business processes** template. The app template already contains a **Financial benefits** section. Rename the section to **Payroll** and add a new **Benefits** section.\nLearn more: [Manage apps](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=2444#title-2232-6).\nFig. 1 Set up app sections\n![Fig.\u00a01 Set up app sections](https://academy.creatio.com/docs/sites/en/files/images/NoCodePlatform/set_up_the_app_ui/scr_set_up_sections.png)\nTo set up the **Payroll** section:\n1. Click ![](https://academy.creatio.com/docs/sites/en/files/images/NoCodePlatform/set_up_the_app_ui/btn_system_designer.png) to **open** the System Designer.\n2. **Go to** the **Application management** block \u2192 **Application Hub**.\n3. **Create** a \"Financial benefits\" app based on **Records & business processes** template. Learn more: [Manage apps](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=2444#title-2232-6).\n4. **Click** **Navigation and sections**.\n5. **Select** the **Financial benefits** section.\n6. **Change** the section color in the **Select icon and color** field. For this example, select light turquoise.\n7. **Change** the section icon in the **Select icon and color** field. For this example, select ![](https://academy.creatio.com/docs/sites/en/files/images/NoCodePlatform/set_up_the_app_ui/icn_payroll.png).\n8. **Enter** **Payroll** in the **Title** field.\n9. **Save the changes**. Fig. 2 Change section color and icon\n![Fig.\u00a02 Change section color and icon](https://academy.creatio.com/docs/sites/academy_en/files/images/NoCodePlatform/set_up_the_app_ui/scr_edit_section.png)\nTo set up the **Benefits** section:\n1. Click ![](https://academy.creatio.com/docs/sites/en/files/images/NoCodePlatform/set_up_the_app_ui/btn_system_designer.png) to **open** the System Designer.\n2. **Go to** the **Application management** block \u2192 **Application Hub**.\n3. **Click** the \"Financial benefits\" app tile.\n4. **Click** **New Freedom UI section**. This opens a window.\n5. **Select** the section color in the **Select icon and color** field. For this example, select dark purple.\n6. **Select** the section icon in the **Select icon and color** field. For this example, select ![](https://academy.creatio.com/docs/sites/en/files/images/NoCodePlatform/set_up_the_app_ui/icn_benefits.png).\n7. **Enter** **Benefits** in the **Title** field.\n8. **Save the changes**.\nAs a result, Creatio will rename the **Financial benefits** section to **Payroll** and add a **Benefits** section as well as the corresponding section object, form page, and list page.\n* * *\n## See also\u200b\n[Create a custom app](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=2377)\n[Freedom UI Designer](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=2376)",
